  "title": "A Hierarchical Concept of Ecosystems: An Alternative to Sector Management for Multi-Species Fisheries",
  "abstract": "Management of multi-species fisheries in New England is based fundamentally on single-species quotas functionally equivalent to those that previously failed to restore fish stocks. The numerous reasons for the inadequacies of quotas as an effective management tool are reviewed. Multi-species management depends upon understanding how fisheries ecosystems are structured and function, but fisheries management lacks a common definition or testable hypothesis of the nature of ecosystems. It is proposed that a hierarchical concept of ecosystems offers a simpler and more effective basis for multi-species fisheries management.",
